{"id": 3418, "title": "Ticket #3418: Have the DAGMAN_USE_STRICT value default to 1?", "description": "<blockquote>\nI'm wondering whether the default for the DAGMAN_USE_STRICT value should be 1 instead of 0.  (Before making this change I think we need to look at the specific warnings that would be affected by it.)  But at least for some stuff, I think it would be a good idea to have things default to fatal errors; and then if you really think the problem should be allowed, you have to explicitly take action to allow it.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2013-Jan-10 12:12:33 by wenger:</em> <br/>\n\nIt might be interesting to crank the strictness up to the max and see if all of the tests work...</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Jan-30 15:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c7088fa5a785b3b0cea80b86e5fad5340e18c7d6\">[34802]</a></span>: modify 7.9.4 version history item. Needed to change because of <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3418\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3418'); return false;\" title=\"Have the DAGMAN_USE_STRICT value default to 1?\">#3418</a></span>. ===GT=== <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"defer\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=1419\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1419'); return false;\" title=\"Warn if log files are in /tmp\">#1419</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Jan-30 12:57</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng